<div id="col2">

	<h2>Things You Can Do With Aardvark</h2>
	<ul>
	<li>Clean up unwanted banners and surrounding "fluff," especially prior to printing a page</li>
	<li>See how the page is created, block by block</li>
	<li>View the source code of one or more elements</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Bookmarklet version:</h2>
	<p>
To run Aardvark as a bookmarklet in Firefox, IE, or Safari, just bookmark the following link:
<br />
<br />
<a href="javascript:document.getElementsByTagName('head')[0].appendChild(document.createElement('script')).setAttribute('src','http://www.karmatics.com/aardvark/bookmarklet.js')">
Aardvark
</a>
<br />
<br />
To do this in Firefox, right click and select "Bookmark this link." In IE, right click and select "Add to Favorites". In Safari, drag the link to the bookmarks bar.
</p>
<p>
Bookmarklets have many advantages for developers.  See the <a href="bookmarklet.html" >bookmarklet page</a> for more info. 
</p>
